{"lemma":"أُسْطُواناتُ","slug":"أُسْطُواناتُ","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19758"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"column","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prism, including cylinder","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"الأسطوانة كل شكل مجسم يحيط به سطحان متوازيان وسطح أو سطوح واصلة بين السطحين المتوازيين"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cylinder"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vinyl record, phonograph record"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic אִיסְטְוָונָא (ʾesṭwānā, “column, pillar”), from Middle Persian [script needed] (stwn' /⁠stūn⁠/, “column, pillar”) (Persian ستون (sotun)), from Old Persian 𐎿𐎬𐎢𐎴𐎠 (s-tu-u-n-a /⁠stūnā⁠/, “column, pillar”), from Proto-Iranian *stuHnáH (“column, pillar”), from Proto-Indo-Iranian *stʰuHnáH (“column, pillar”), from Proto-Indo-European *sth₂-uh₂-néh₂, from *steh₂- (“to stand”) + *-wéh₂ (deverbal adjective suffix), + *-néh₂."},"ipa":["/ʔus.tˤu.waː.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19758","headword_ar":"اُسْطُوَانَةٌ","root":"sTn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of well-known meaning, (S, L,) arabicized from [the Pers.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usotuwino","text_ar":"اُسْتُوِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies the same], (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAriyapN","text_ar":"سَارِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A column, of stone"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of baked bricks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, L, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaATiynu","text_ar":"اَسَاطِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * L, Msb, K *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usoTuwaAnaAtN","text_ar":"اُسْطُوَانَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufoEuwaAlapN","text_ar":"اُفْعُوَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, Msb, K,) because its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaATaynu","text_ar":"اَسَاطَينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"being radical, (L, Msb,) accord. to Kh (Msb) and Fr, who says that it is the only instance of this measure; (L;) or of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEoluwaAnapN","text_ar":"فُعْلُوَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) accord. to Akh, but, (J says, L,) if so, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is augmentative and has next to it two augmentative letters, and this is scarcely ever, or never, the case; (S, L;) IB, however, says that this is the true measure, as is shown by its pl.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaATiynu","text_ar":"اَسَاطِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and its dim., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usayoTiynapN","text_ar":"اُسَيْطِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) accord. to some, it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufoEulaAnapN","text_ar":"اُفْعُلَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, Msb,) but, if it were so, it would not have for its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaATiynu","text_ar":"اَسَاطِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as there is no instance of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afaAEiynu","text_ar":"اَفَاعِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L.) ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portico."},{"kind":"text","text":"Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu AlA^usoTuwaAnapi","text_ar":"اَهْلُ الاُسْطُوَانَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Stoics."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cylinder."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"legs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a beast: (K:) [or rather the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaATiynu","text_ar":"اَسَاطِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has this meaning. (L.) ―         -b5-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"penis."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","M","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}